<Paragraph  FontFamily="Calibri"  FontSize="14">
The following automatic layout features are available in the diagram control:
</Paragraph> 
<Paragraph > <Bold>Organization Chart  </Bold> - This sample demonstrates how to automatically arrange nodes using a directed-tree layout.</Paragraph>

<Paragraph > <Bold>Hierarchical Tree Layout </Bold> - This sample demonstrates how to automatically arrange nodes using a hierarchical-tree layout, which allows a child node to have multiple parent nodes. Cyclic paths are also supported.</Paragraph>

<Paragraph > <Bold>Bowtie Layout </Bold> - This sample demonstrates how to automatically arrange nodes using a Bowtie layout which allows to accessing any type risk.</Paragraph>

<Paragraph > <Bold>Radial Tree Layout</Bold> - This sample demonstrates how to automatically arrange nodes using a radial-tree layout.</Paragraph>

<Paragraph > <Bold>Table Layout  </Bold> - This sample demonstrates how to automatically arrange nodes in a table-like manner using the Table Layout.</Paragraph>

<Paragraph > <Bold>Layout Bounds  </Bold> - This sample demonstrates how to Arrnange layout using LayoutBonds Property.</Paragraph>

